			"notes": [
				{
					"category": "description",
					"text": "A privilege escalation flaw was found in ArgoCD. This flaw allows a malicious user who has push access to an application's source git or Helm repository, or sync and override access, to perform actions they are not authorized to do. \r\n\r\nFor example, if the attacker has `update` or `delete` access, they can modify or delete any resource on the destination cluster and escalate ArgoCD privileges to the admin level. If the attacker has `get` access, they can view and list actions for any resource on the destination cluster except secrets and view the logs of any pods on the destination cluster. If the attacker has action/{some action or *} access on the application, they can run an action for any resource that supports the allowed action on the application's destination cluster.",
					"title": "Vulnerability description"
				},
				{
					"category": "summary",
					"text": "Openshift-Gitops: Improper access control allows admin privilege escalation",
					"title": "Vulnerability summary"
				},
				{
					"category": "general",
					"text": "The CVSS score(s) listed for this vulnerability do not reflect the associated product's status, and are included for informational purposes to better understand the severity of this vulnerability.",
					"title": "CVSS score applicability"
				}
			],
